data.text:
April 1940: Meeting up with the president of the united states, hopefully we can make an agreement to take down Germany Mr. President: Ah, Yes Mr. Stalin I will make sure my secret service tends to your needs May 1940: Listen to My 5 year plans they will help us get out of this depression, were are behind the rest of the world by so many years and we must work together to become number 1 Married to Ekaterina Svanidze 18 December 1878

Wall II The Germans will pay for invading Russia! August 1942:The Germans will pay for invading Russia! Russian Soldier: I could not agree more! July 1940:The French Shall help us in our War against the Germans 10235 people like this French Soldier: Bonjour Monsieur Stalin, we shall fight for you as we fight for our own leader! French Soldier: I agree we must defeat the Germans

Wall III I have Decided On collective farms as one of my 5 year plan Goals Russian Citizen: I Think these would help out our economy, it will create more jobs Peasant: Thank you Prime Minister it will give me a chance to make some money again One More announcement ANY surplus crops you make, you are able to sell and keep the profits for your self Russian Farmer: Thank you, now I am able to afford new cloths and a nicer place for my family

Wall IV Just met a wonderful girl named Ekaterina Svanidze Ekaterina Svanidze: Can’t wait to see you again stalin your not as bad as they say We shall destroy the germans for going against us! Nazi Soldier: Good Luck, Can’t wait to kill you

Wall V If the opposition disarms, all is well and good. If it refuses to disarm, we shall disarm our selves Russian Citizen: Well put Stalin! Russian Soldier: We Shall destroy our opposition Not Disarm THEM!!!

Profile Hanging out with the Bolsheviks Male 18 December 1878 Telling people what to do Gori, Tiflis Governorate, Classical Music Maried to Ekaterina Svanidze The Soviet Network Chapaev Communist Party of the Soviet Union Frankenstein none I wish that I could just tell every one in the world what to do and they would listen… because if they don’t listen I might have to kill them.
